Schroder Investment Management Group Cut Its Automatic Data Processing Common Stock Usd0.10 (ADP) Stake, Harte Hanks (HHS)’s Sentiment Is 0.5


					
						July 24, 2017 - By Nellie Frank

Harte Hanks, Inc. is a multi-channel marketing company. The company has market cap of $60.14 million. The Company’s Customer Interaction business offers a range of marketing services, in media from direct mail to e-mail, including agency and digital services; database marketing solutions and business-to-business lead generation; direct mail, and contact centers. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s agency services are customer engagement agencies specializing in direct and digital communications for both consumer and business-to-business markets.







Schroder Investment Management Group decreased Automatic Data Processing Incorporated Common Stock Usd0.10 (ADP) stake by 75.85% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Schroder Investment Management Group sold 689,331 shares as Automatic Data Processing Incorporated Common Stock Usd0.10 (ADP)’s stock declined 1.06%. The Schroder Investment Management Group holds 219,465 shares with $22.56 million value, down from 908,796 last quarter. Automatic Data Processing Incorporated Common Stock Usd0.10 now has $46.70B valuation. The stock declined 1.37% or $1.43 reaching $103.15 per share. About 1.17M shares traded. Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) has risen 15.83% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 0.87% the S&P500.
Eidelman Virant Capital holds 3.09% of its portfolio in Harte Hanks Inc for 3.58 million shares. Boothbay Fund Management Llc owns 326,896 shares or 0.16% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Redmond Asset Management Llc has 0.16% invested in the company for 225,413 shares. The Massachusetts-based Grt Capital Partners L.L.C. has invested 0.06% in the stock. Columbia Asset Management, a Michigan-based fund reported 1,500 shares.
Analysts await Harte Hanks Inc (NYSE:HHS) to report earnings on August, 8. They expect $-0.03 earnings per share, up 57.14% or $0.04 from last year’s $-0.07 per share. After $-0.53 actual earnings per share reported by Harte Hanks Inc for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -94.34% EPS growth. 
 It is down 8.47% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 8.23% the S&P500.
Since January 25, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 9 selling transactions for $21.89 million activity. Another trade for 24,028 shares valued at $2.44M was made by Ayala John on Friday, January 27. O’Brien Dermot J had sold 23,036 shares worth $2.38M. The insider Rodriguez Carlos A sold $7.88M. Albinson Brock also sold $42,108 worth of Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) shares. Another trade for 5,688 shares valued at $594,150 was made by JONES JOHN P III on Wednesday, March 1. Perrotti Thomas J sold $301,197 worth of Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) on Friday, March 17. The insider Eberhard Michael C sold 7,463 shares worth $783,615.
Schroder Investment Management Group increased Bridgepoint Education Incorporated Common Stock Usd0.01 (NYSE:BPI) stake by 296,639 shares to 870,096 valued at $8.81 million in 2016Q4. It also upped Aramark Common Stock Usd0.01 (NYSE:ARMK) stake by 170,381 shares and now owns 3.74M shares. Rlj Lodging Trust Reit Npv (NYSE:RLJ) was raised too. 
Analysts await Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) to report earnings on July, 27 before the open. They expect $0.67 EPS, down 2.90% or $0.02 from last year’s $0.69 per share. ADP’s profit will be $303.33M for 38.49 P/E if the $0.67 EPS becomes a reality. After $1.31 actual EPS reported by Automatic Data Processing for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -48.85% negative EPS growth. 
Among 15 analysts covering Automatic Data (NASDAQ:ADP), 2 have Buy rating, 3 Sell and 10 Hold. Therefore 13% are positive. Automatic Data had 22 analyst reports since August 3, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was downgraded by William Blair on Friday, July 21 to “Market Perform”. Robert W. Baird downgraded it to “Neutral” rating and $94 target in Friday, July 29 report. Compass Point initiated Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) rating on Friday, April 15. Compass Point has “Sell” rating and $76 target. The stock of Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) has “Hold” rating given on Monday, January 30 by Stifel Nicolaus. The rating was downgraded by Barclays Capital to “Equal-Weight” on Tuesday, July 18. The stock of Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) earned “Sector Perform” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Thursday, February 4. JP Morgan maintained the shares of ADP in report on Friday, August 14 with “Neutral” rating. The firm has “Neutral” rating by Goldman Sachs given on Tuesday, June 20. As per Monday, July 11, the company rating was upgraded by Bernstein. The stock of Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) has “Outperform” rating given on Monday, August 31 by William Blair.








