Schroder Investment Management Group Trimmed Its Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited Ads Representing 5 Common Shares (TSM) Stake by $3.74 Million as Shares Rose


					

						July 13, 2017 - By Migdalia James

Schroder Investment Management Group decreased its stake in Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited Ads Representing 5 Common Shares (TSM) by 0.67% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Schroder Investment Management Group sold 133,537 shares as the company’s stock rose 8.84% with the market. The institutional investor held 19.76M shares of the semiconductors company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $567.98M, down from 19.89 million at the end of the previous reported quarter. Schroder Investment Management Group who had been investing in Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited Ads Representing 5 Common Shares for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $182.49 billion market cap company. The stock rose 1.18% or $0.42 reaching $36.11. About 7.73 million shares traded or 9.49% up from the average. Taiwan Semiconductor Mfg. Co. Ltd. (ADR) (NYSE:TSM) has risen 51.40% since July 13, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 34.70% the S&P500.






Schroder Investment Management Group, which manages about $42.96 billion and $52.24B US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Churchill Downs Inc (NASDAQ:CHDN) by 25,494 shares to 89,641 shares, valued at $13.49 million in 2016Q4, according to the filing. It also increased its holding in Sonoco Products Company Common Stock Npv (NYSE:SON) by 126,054 shares in the quarter, for a total of 1.98 million shares, and has risen its stake in Range Resources Corporation Common Stock Usd0.01 (NYSE:RRC). 
More recent Taiwan Semiconductor Mfg. Co. Ltd. (ADR) (NYSE:TSM) news were published by: Benzinga.com which released: “Fast Money Traders Share Their Chip Picks” on July 13, 2017. Also Benzinga.com published the news titled: “6 Stocks To Watch For July 13, 2017” on July 13, 2017. Benzinga.com‘s news article titled: “22 Stocks Moving In Thursday’s Pre-Market Session” with publication date: July 13, 2017 was also an interesting one.
Taiwan Semiconductor Mfg. Co. Ltd. (ADR) (NYSE:TSM) Ratings Coverage
Among 5 analysts covering Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing (NYSE:TSM), 1 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 4 Hold. Therefore 20% are positive. Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing had 9 analyst reports since August 24, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Outperform” rating by Credit Suisse given on Friday, December 11. Susquehanna upgraded Taiwan Semiconductor Mfg. Co. Ltd. (ADR) (NYSE:TSM) on Tuesday, October 4 to “Neutral” rating. The rating was upgraded by Pacific Crest to “Sector Weight” on Friday, October 14. HSBC downgraded the stock to “Hold” rating in Thursday, October 13 report. The rating was downgraded by HSBC on Wednesday, June 21 to “Hold”. The firm earned “Neutral” rating on Tuesday, June 28 by Goldman Sachs.


