Schroder Investment Management Group Acquires 13,444 Shares of EPAM Systems, Inc. (EPAM)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 5th, 2017 // No Comments




Schroder Investment Management Group raised its stake in shares of  EPAM Systems, Inc. (NYSE:EPAM) by 8.7% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 167,445 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock after buying an additional 13,444 shares during the period. Schroder Investment Management Group owned 0.33% of EPAM Systems worth $12,712,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other hedge funds have also modified their holdings of EPAM. Conatus Capital Management LP increased its position in  EPAM Systems by 3.9% in the third quarter. Conatus Capital Management LP now owns 955,475 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock worth $66,224,000 after buying an additional 35,868 shares during the period.  State Street Corp increased its position in  EPAM Systems by 1.4% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 885,457 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock worth $56,943,000 after buying an additional 11,804 shares during the period.  GW&K Investment Management LLC increased its position in  EPAM Systems by 23.6% in the first quarter. GW&K Investment Management LLC now owns 561,695 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock worth $42,419,000 after buying an additional 107,151 shares during the period.  Russell Investments Group Ltd. increased its position in  EPAM Systems by 43.1% in the first quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. now owns 491,593 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock worth $37,125,000 after buying an additional 148,146 shares during the period.  Finally, Bloom Tree Partners LLC increased its position in  EPAM Systems by 69.8% in the third quarter. Bloom Tree Partners LLC now owns 351,188 shares of the information technology services provider’s stock worth $24,341,000 after buying an additional 144,366 shares during the period. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  97.75% of the company’s stock. 


