Schroders plc is a British multinational asset management company, founded in 1804. The company employs over 4,100 people worldwide across 41 offices in 27 different countries around Europe, America, Asia, Africa and the Middle East. Headquartered in the City of London, it is traded on the London Stock Exchange and is a constituent of the FTSE 100 Index. Schroders has two share classes: voting shares (SDR.L) and non-voting shares (SDRC.L).
